One common situation where poor digital communication causes problems is when a student sends an unprofessional email to a professor without a proper subject line, greeting, or clear message. 
This can create confusion and may even lead to the email being ignored.
Effective communication requires clarity, proper structure, and respectful tone. Using a clear subject line, addressing the recipient properly, and writing a concise message can make communication more effective. 
Additionally, proofreading emails before sending them helps avoid mistakes.
This task helped me understand the importance of professional email etiquette and responsible communication. 
Following these practices ensures better understanding and creates a positive impression in academic and professional environments.
